# GRIMSEC DevSecOps Agent Suite

12 specialized security agents covering the complete DevSecOps lifecycle. Each agent auto-activates based on trigger phrases — just describe what you want in natural language.

## Agent Index

| # | Agent | File | Triggers On |
|---|-------|------|-------------|
| 1 | **Repo Analyzer** | `grimsec-repo-analyzer.mdc` | "analyze this repo", "security scan", "vulnerability assessment", "threat model", "DevSecOps analysis" |
| 2 | **CI/CD Auditor** | `grimsec-cicd-auditor.mdc` | "audit GitHub Actions", "CI/CD security", "workflow security", "supply chain attack" |
| 3 | **Vuln Enricher** | `grimsec-vuln-enricher.mdc` | "look up CVE", "enrich vulnerabilities", "EPSS score", "CISA KEV", "ATT&CK mapping" |
| 4 | **Doc Intel** | `grimsec-doc-intel.mdc` | "analyze documentation", "product context", "security architecture", "validate finding" |
| 5 | **Threat Monitor** | `grimsec-threat-monitor.mdc` | "new CVEs", "monitor vulnerabilities", "threat intel", "exposure check" |
| 6 | **Executive Reporter** | `grimsec-executive-reporter.mdc` | "executive report", "security ROI", "risk quantification", "compliance mapping", "CISO report" |
| 7 | **DAST Scanner** | `grimsec-dast-scanner.mdc` | "DAST", "dynamic testing", "ZAP scan", "Nuclei scan", "web app security testing" |
| 8 | **Exploit Validator** | `grimsec-exploit-validator.mdc` | "exploit validation", "PoC generation", "prove exploitability", "validate finding" |
| 9 | **Code Understanding** | `grimsec-code-understanding.mdc` | "map attack surface", "trace dataflow", "hunt variants", "explain framework security" |
| 10 | **IaC Policy** | `grimsec-iac-policy.mdc` | "scan IaC", "Checkov", "OPA policy", "CIS benchmark", "Terraform security", "K8s security" |
| 11 | **Forensics** | `grimsec-forensics.mdc` | "investigate repo", "forensic analysis", "supply chain compromise", "package backdoored" |
| 12 | **Adversary Sim** | `grimsec-adversary-sim.mdc` | "adversary simulation", "red team", "penetration testing", "kill chain", "ATT&CK mapping" |

## Standard Pipeline Flow

```
Repo Analyzer (1)
  ├── CI/CD Auditor (2)      — audit the pipeline
  ├── Vuln Enricher (3)      — enrich CVEs with EPSS/KEV/ATT&CK
  ├── Doc Intel (4)          — validate findings against docs
  ├── Threat Monitor (5)     — continuous exposure monitoring
  ├── DAST Scanner (7)       — runtime testing
  ├── Exploit Validator (8)  — prove high-risk findings
  ├── Code Understanding (9) — deep code analysis
  ├── IaC Policy (10)        — infrastructure compliance
  ├── Forensics (11)         — supply chain investigation
  └── Adversary Sim (12)     — red team simulation
          │
          ▼
  Executive Reporter (6)     — board/CISO-level report
```

## Output Convention

All analysis artifacts are written to `./grimsec-output/` relative to your project root:

```
grimsec-output/
├── {repo-name}/             # Per-repo analysis (Agents 1-5, 7-10)
│   ├── inventory.json
│   ├── app-context.json
│   ├── scan-results/
│   ├── reachability-analysis.json
│   ├── remediation.json
│   └── assessment-report.md
├── threat-intel/            # Agent 5 output
├── executive/               # Agent 6 output
├── exploit-validation/      # Agent 8 output
├── code-understanding/      # Agent 9 output
├── iac-policy/              # Agent 10 output
├── forensics/               # Agent 11 output
└── adversary-simulation/    # Agent 12 output
```

